Nightingale

Ambient Nursing Intelligence System

Product thesis

Hospitals do not have a nursing shortage as much as a nursing attention shortage.

Nurses are forced to spend too much of their best cognition on:
	•	redundant charting
	•	reconciliation across screens
	•	remembering the shift timeline
	•	hunting for missing documentation
	•	translating reality into EHR form language

So Nightingale should not be “an AI note writer.”

It should be a clinical memory and operations layer that sits between care and the chart.

Its job is to turn:

what happened
→ into
what must be remembered
→ into
what must be documented
→ into
what must be watched next


