4. Core system behavior

The golden workflow

Step 1: Observe

Nightingale listens to structured and semi-structured signals:
	•	nurse voice
	•	monitor data
	•	BCMA scans
	•	device feeds
	•	orders/labs context
	•	location/task context
	•	prior chart state

Step 2: Convert to event objects

Everything becomes a timestamped clinical event.

Example:

{
  "event_type": "mobility",
  "timestamp": "2026-03-14T10:42:00",
  "patient_id": "P123",
  "nurse_id": "N771",
  "source": ["voice_capture", "room_exit_context"],
  "data": {
    "activity": "ambulated to bathroom",
    "assist_level": "one assist",
    "response": "tolerated well"
  },
  "confidence": 0.91
}

Step 3: Update patient state

The event engine updates the longitudinal patient model.

Step 4: Draft artifacts

The composer prepares:
	•	flowsheet entries
	•	narrative notes
	•	reminders
	•	handoff elements
	•	risk deltas

Step 5: Nurse verifies

Nurse is always final signer.

