7. AI architecture

Model stack

A. Clinical speech recognition

Custom ASR tuned for:
	•	noisy rooms
	•	abbreviations
	•	med names
	•	accents
	•	interrupted dictation

B. Clinical NLP parser

Turns text/audio into:
	•	entities
	•	assessments
	•	interventions
	•	response relations
	•	chart destinations

C. Temporal reasoning engine

Understands order and dependency:
	•	med given
	•	reassessment due
	•	patient response follows
	•	risk window opens/closes

D. Summarization engine

Generates:
	•	note drafts
	•	handoffs
	•	care summaries
	•	patient-friendly explanations

E. Risk pattern engine

Hybrid rules + ML.

Why hybrid:
	•	rules for high-trust compliance loops
	•	ML for weak pattern emergence
	•	explainability is critical

F. Confidence and provenance layer

Every suggestion carries:
	•	what source generated it
	•	whether direct or inferred
	•	confidence score
	•	evidence trace

This must be first-class, not a hidden developer detail.

