19. Canonical PRD skeleton

Product requirements document

Problem

Nurses spend too much time reconstructing and documenting care manually, causing cognitive overload, omission risk, and reduced bedside care.

Goal

Reduce documentation burden while increasing documentation quality and preserving nurse authority.

Users

Bedside nurses first; charge nurses second.

Core use cases
	•	voice capture note drafting
	•	shift summary generation
	•	handoff generation
	•	pain reassessment loop completion
	•	chart gap detection
	•	change-only charting

Must-haves
	•	editable drafts
	•	provenance
	•	audit logs
	•	EHR integration
	•	mobile speed
	•	zero fabrication tolerance

Non-goals
	•	autonomous diagnosis
	•	autonomous chart signing
	•	order entry authority
	•	broad conversational agent as primary UI

